lender.name: John Beck Hofmann
lender.loan_because:
Weve all witnessed the destructive power of our current banking structure and system of credit and how these institutions have enslaved billions of people to a life of debt. I want to do something to lessen the power these institutions have over peoples lives - people who are merely wanting to create a better life for themselves.
Making loans available to people who might never qualify for one, or have the means to pay it back anytime soon- taking the opportunity to help create a business for someone that would provide for their family- its a very rewarding thing to see.
I love the idea that people from all walks of life, can contribute as a group, and fund individuals all over the world. We all have something to contribute to the whole. This is how lending should work. This is the way a truly civilized global society should work. As former US president JFK said nearly 50 years ago "Our most basic common link is that we all inhabit this small planet. We all breathe the same air. We all cherish our children's future. And we are all mortal."
